@startuml
title PB-428 UC12 View fund details

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #000000
  LifeLineBorderColor #666666
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #666666
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #E9ECF6
  BoxBorderColor #666666
  BoxBackgroundColor #DDDDDD
  NoteBorderColor #666666
  NoteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
}

' Abstract box at top
rectangle "Abstract:\nThis use case will return fund details for a single fund. This is an existing endpoint and we\nwill add additional response fields to this endpoint. They include:\n1. FundCategory (new)\n2. RequireFundTC (new)\n3. RiskScore (existing field in table, but needs to be added in response)\n4. IncomeValue (new)\n5. IncomeDescription (new)\n6. isNextSimples (new)" as ABSTRACT #white

actor "Next Customer" as NC

box "Next Platform" #DDDDDD
  participant "Core Next" as CN
  database "Next Database" as ND
end box

participant "Core Bradesco" as CB

NC -> CN : HTTP\n1 GET /investments/funds/completeDetails
activate CN

note left of CN
The App will make a call
to Core Next to get all the
details for a fund. It will
pass required input:
- Fund ID
end note

note left of CN #FFA500
<b>Note to Dev</b>
Please check if the input
parameter Fund ID is the
Product ID or the External_
Core_Product_ID. From what
I can see, there are two
product records with the
same External_Core_Product_ID
(Next Simples) and this may
create issues.
end note

ref over CN
Use existing methodology to get
complete details for a fund.
end ref

CN -> ND : 2 GET additional fields from Product table
activate ND
ND --> CN : 3 Response
deactivate ND

note right of CN
Core Next will retrieve additional
data from the PRODUCT table and return
them to the App:
1. FundCategory (new)
2. RequireFundTC (new)
3. RiskScore (existing field in table,
   but needs to be added in response)
4. IncomeValue (new)
5. IncomeDescription (new)
6. isNextSimples (new)
end note

CN --> NC : 4 Response
deactivate CN

note left of CN
Core Next will return all
existing fields in the response
+ the following new response
fields:
1. FundCategory (new)
2. RequireFundTC (new)
3. RiskScore (existing field in table,
   but needs to be added in response)
4. IncomeValue (new)
5. IncomeDescription (new)
6. isNextSimples (new)

All of these fields will come
from the PRODUCT table.
end note

@enduml